  "local_port": 58622,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What can I do with an infant at Walt Disney World?",
  "response": "Walt Disney World can be a magical place for families with infants, and there's plenty to do to ensure everyone has a fun and comfortable experience. Here are some tips and suggestions:\n\n### General Tips\n1. **Stroller Rental**: Disney offers stroller rentals, which can be very helpful. Rentals can be done at the parks or in advance online.\n2. **Baby Care Centers**: Each park has a Baby Care Center where you can change diapers, feed your baby, and even buy baby supplies.\n3. **Rider Switch**: If there's an attraction both parents want to experience but it's not suitable for infants, use the Rider Switch service. One parent can ride while the other waits with the baby, then they can switch without waiting in line again.\n4. **Early Entry**: Take advantage of early entry for resort guests to enjoy attractions with shorter lines.\n\n### Park-Specific Activities\n#### Magic Kingdom\n- **It's a Small World**: A gentle boat ride with colorful visuals and music.\n- **Dumbo the Flying Elephant**: A classic ride that's usually enjoyable for infants.\n- **The Many Adventures of Winnie the Pooh**: A dark ride that's soothing and features familiar characters.\n\n#### Epcot\n- **Frozen Ever After**: A gentle boat ride with fun characters and music.\n- **Gran Fiesta Tour Starring The Three Caballeros**: Another boat ride that's calm and visually appealing.\n\n#### Disney's Hollywood Studios\n- **Mickey & Minnie's Runaway Railway**: A charming dark ride that can be enjoyable for infants.\n- **Toy Story Land**: While some attractions might be too intense, the atmosphere and photo ops are great.\n\n#### Disney's Animal Kingdom\n- **Kilimanjaro Safaris**: A slow-moving safari ride where you can see animals from your seat.\n- **Na'vi River Journey**: A calm boat ride with beautiful visuals and sounds.\n\n### Dining\n- **Character Dining**: Experiences like the Crystal Palace or Chef Mickey's can be fun, though infants may not remember the characters, parents can enjoy the experience.\n- **Baby Food and Purees**: You can bring your own or buy at the Baby Care Centers.\n\n### Shows and Parades\n- **Parades and Fireworks**: These can be enjoyable for parents, and infants can sleep through them in a stroller. Just be mindful of noise levels.\n- **Live Shows**: Shows like Finding Nemo: The Big Blue... and Beyond! at Animal Kingdom are family-friendly and have seating suitable for strollers.\n\n### Other Tips\n- **Comfortable Clothing**: Dress your infant in comfortable clothing and pack extra outfits.\n- **Hydration and Snacks**: Keep your infant hydrated and fed, and don't forget snacks for yourself.\n- **Rest Times**: Schedule nap times and breaks to keep everyone happy and rested.\n\nOverall, Walt Disney World can be a wonderful experience for families with infants, as long as you plan ahead and take advantage of the resources available. Enjoy your magical trip!",
